Hello
add one line for change
open this file via vim
how can i save a file while using text editor vim
you can save by press esc and type :w
this mean write into
or you can save and quit using :wq!
this mean write into and quit
if you want quit but no saving
you can type :q!
if you want to undo the text you write in
you can type :undo
finally, if you want to find words in the text
type :/words and the cursor will place to the line that contain the words
remember press esc to type the command to vim editor!
bye
